×


Mike Chang


Mike Chang has over 25 years of IT experience in Services, Sales, Business Development and Solution Selling. Proven track record on revenue growth in Software and Services. Very familiar with Taiwan market, customers and partners ecosystem. With strong business and technical experiences on value selling for Internet of things (IoT), big data, Machine learning, IBM Watson cognitive, Mobile Services, API economy, Hybrid cloud in IBM Cloud and also well know Microsoft all of products and Cloud Azure, office365 services. 

Specialties: C-Level engagement skill to customer in Cloud Digital Transformation, Industry trend and company’s point of view, unique value. Pitch marketing message and Deliver speech to public event in many areas – Cloud platform, big data, Internet of Things (IoT), LoRa, and Cognitive Watson solution. Domain expertise in new technology trend- Blockchain, Fintech, Industry 4.0, Robot, and IoT

Mike Chang is a former Cloud Adoption Leader with experience across many of the IBM Cloud products and services including Bluemix, Infrastructure, Watson, API Connect, Blockchain, , VMware, Cloud Foundry, OpenStack, Container technologies (Docker, Kubernetes), Bluemix Garage, etc.  

Mike is an IBM Cloud Advisor, with Master Level, Certified Solution Advisor and certified IBM Design Thinking Practitioner

Prior to IBM, Mike worked for Microsoft with 15 years working experiences, had Leadership Experience on MS Enterprise Services Functional lead at Taiwan, Managed Services team P&L with 70 peoples scale business group. And also have experience on pre-sell lead as technical solution sales lead at Microsoft technology center as director. In change of MS Innovation Technology and Cloud Services to help customer building enterprise end to end solution, partnership with hardware & software vendors. 

Familiars with Microsoft technology include Internet of things (IOT), Big Data, Machine learning , Cloud Services (Azure IaaS, PaaS, SaaS, Hybrid cloud), Media Services, SAP on Azure, Modern datacenter, Enterprise UC&C and Social , Mobile Devices to apply different Industries.









ST Liew
VP and President, Qualcomm Taiwan Qualcomm
Qualcomm






×


ST Liew


ST Liew began his position as Vice President and President of Qualcomm Taiwan in October of 2016, responsible for Qualcomm’s businesses in Taiwan. Liew has more than 30 years of experience leading business and engineering teams in the telecommunications industry. Most recently, Liew was Co-President of Acer Inc.’s Smart Products Business Group, which focused on smartphones, tablets and wearable devices. Under his leadership, smartphone and tablet volumes grew several folds. Prior to that, Liew was the Associate Vice President of Acer’s EMEA Smartphone Business Unit.

Before joining Acer, Liew worked at Motorola where he held several business and technical roles, including leading Motorola’s design centers as well as in product management, product development, manufacturing and test engineering. Liew spent many years in Motorola responsible for a variety of R&D projects ranging from walkie-talkie, pagers and cellular products in markets all over the world. 

Liew received his MBA from the National University of Singapore, and holds a BSc. in Electrical and Electronic Engineering from the University of Leeds, UK.








