Brad Lynch
VP, Product Development
Peraso Technologies Inc.






×


Brad Lynch


Mr. Lynch brings 20 years of communications product development experience, including 15 years of specific semiconductor IC development. As Senior VP, Product Development at Peraso Technologies, Mr. Lynch is responsible for Peraso’s WiGig product roadmap. In addition, Mr. Lynch has responsibility for all digital IC and software development. During his time at Peraso, Mr. Lynch has been a key contributor to the WiGig, 802.11ad and 802.11ay specifications. Prior to founding Peraso, Mr. Lynch was a founder of Cogency Semiconductor, a fabless semiconductor company focused on the development of modems for powerline networking. At Cogency, Mr. Lynch was primarily responsible for driving the system architecture. In this role, he made significant technical contributions to the HomePlug Powerline specification, and was recognized by the organization as a HomePlug Fellow. Upon the Intellon acquisition of Cogency, Mr. Lynch became the Director of Software Engineering at Intellon.











